On Fri, 29 Apr 2005, Seann Stafford wrote:

> My question is this:
> where do you Hammies and/or CB'ers (yes I know that they are
> not interchangeable) mount your antennae?  Do you bolt or
> clamp or use a magnet as my father used to?  Seems to me the
> motor in the waaaaay back and the rest of the ignition in the
> waaaay front posed some interesting factors...

Mag mounts are useful for small VHF/UHF antennas if you have a metal roof.
HF antennas just about need a hard mount.  A roof rack is the only way to
fly for this!

